      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The incoming feeders must comply with the
general recommendation of IEC or the general standards applicable
for the local electrical regulations.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">When connecting <ph platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/ph ">the rectifier mains</ph>
               <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">the
DC input</ph>
               <ph otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/ph "> and the bypass mains</ph> consider that:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">All wiring must comply with all applicable local and/or national
electrical codes.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The inputs must be protected by external fuses or MCCBs.<note class="- topic/note ">Minimum fuse/MCCB protection rating is specified in the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical
Data</i>. Higher rating might be needed to comply with local and/or
national electrical codes.</note>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check the voltage
and frequency on rating plate.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Pay attention
to the phase rotation.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Pay attention to the DC input power supply polarity.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The person carrying out the work must be an authorized electrician.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
